# Worker-scope secrets — the ONE Claude credential powering planner + workers.
# Lives as PLAINTEXT secret.worker.env in the workspace (seeded from this template by
# init/setup). It is gitignored — never commit it — and chmod 600 is recommended.
# Pick ONE billing mode below.

# ── Option A (RECOMMENDED if you have Pro/Max): use your SUBSCRIPTION quota, no metered API ──
# Generate a 1-year OAuth token (requires a Pro/Max/Team/Enterprise plan):
#     claude setup-token
# then paste it below. IMPORTANT: if you use this, leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY UNSET / blank —
# Claude Code's auth precedence makes ANTHROPIC_API_KEY win and forces metered API billing
# (secret_exec also strips the API key defensively when the OAuth token is present).
# Note: planner (`claude -p`) usage draws on your monthly Agent SDK credit; interactive workers
# draw on your regular interactive limits. A big parallel fleet can deplete these fast.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# ── Option B: pay-as-you-go metered API ──
# Use a DISPOSABLE, minimally-scoped key (NOT your personal key) so a leak is one quick revoke.
# A fleet loop on metered billing can get expensive — see README "token-burn guardrails".
# Leave this BLANK to use Option A.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
